line_2: To Sing Ramillia's Day! to which must yield
Cannae's Illustrious Fight, and Fam'd Pharsalia's Field.

line_1: In ev'ry Rule of happy Writings skill'd;
line_2: O born with Genius, and with Learning fill'd,

line_1: Renown'd for Conquest, and in Council skill'd,
line_2: Polish'd in Courts, and harden'd in the Field,

line_1: Cecilia, more than all the Muses skill'd!
line_2: Cecilia comes, with holy Rapture fill'd,

line_1: Cecilia, more than all the Muses skill'd!
line_2: Phoebus himself to her must yield,

line_1: Cecilia, more than all the Muses skill'd!
line_2: Phoebus himself to her must yield,

line_1: In learned Languages had she been skill'd,
line_2: Still with your Praises had our School been fill'd.

line_1: No wonder then, if nicely skill'd
In all the Labyrinths of Logic skill'd,
line_2: She taught the subtle Reas'ner not to yield;

line_1: Nor see her Sons in Science skill'd,
line_2: And yet her Posts by Strangers fill'd.

line_1: Succeeding Bards in rural Secrets skill'd,
line_2: Shall teach the Swain t'enrich the barren Field;

line_1: Wretches, who only in Destruction skill'd,
line_2: Try to pull down, what they could ne're rebuild;

line_1: You, Psecas, know, in seedy Labour skill'd,
line_2: What various Herbage fatten'd Pastures yield,

line_1: You, Psecas, know, in seedy Labour skill'd,
line_2: And what unnumber'd Kinds adorn the Field,

line_1: Or who in jousts and tourneys skill'd,
line_2: Or with heav'd poll-axe clear'd the field,
